## Agent General Staff Execution Rules

This project is AGS-governed. Keep user-authored Claude instructions outside
this managed block. AGS may update only the marked block.

Claude Code role:
- Consume bounded task cards formed from confirmed execution contracts.
- Read `AGENTS.md`, this file, and the canonical protocol files before execution.
- Do not form Light / Medium / Heavy classifications from raw user requests.
- Do not generate executable task cards from raw requests or from `方案 OK` alone.
- If the first non-empty line is `## 任务卡`, validate it first: a valid existing card goes directly to policy resolution and runner consumption; invalid card-shaped input fails closed and never falls through to task-card generation.
- Task-card permission has exactly two modes: `plan-only` and `execute-and-verify`.
- Heavy defaults to `plan-only`; an explicit Heavy `execute-and-verify` card executes and verifies directly, with an independent review gate.
- On resume or `继续`, reread the task card, run `git status --short`, and preserve its declared permission mode.
- Do not install hooks, dependencies, runner adapters, or production wiring unless the task card explicitly authorizes it.
- Do not run destructive git commands or touch secrets unless explicitly authorized.
- Complete the narrowest relevant verification and report evidence before claiming completion.

Canonical references:
- `protocol/agent-task-protocol.md`
- `protocol/task-routing.md`
- `protocol/runtime-adapters.md`
- `protocol/task-card-template.md`
